1
00:00:04,368 --> 00:00:08,600
Oh, here's little Ben falling asleep.

2
00:00:08,806 --> 00:00:13,436
A little bit later. Is he gonna sleep?

3
00:00:13,644 --> 00:00:18,479
Is he gonna sleep? Is he gonna?

4
00:00:18,782 --> 00:00:21,512
Yep, out like a light!

5
00:00:21,885 --> 00:00:25,343
This sure trumps
the "Has he pooped?" series.

6
00:00:25,556 --> 00:00:27,387
Ross, we love him, okay?

7
00:00:27,591 --> 00:00:30,651
But right now he's just
a little fat guy.

8
00:00:30,861 --> 00:00:32,385
How excited can we get?

9
00:00:34,932 --> 00:00:37,958
-What you got?
-400 pictures of Ben on a rug.

10
00:00:38,168 --> 00:00:41,160
-Oh, my God!
-Let me see!

11
00:00:42,439 --> 00:00:44,634
The One Where Rachel Finds Out

12
00:01:27,651 --> 00:01:29,949
Here's little Ben nodding off.

13
00:01:30,154 --> 00:01:32,884
Look at Aunt Monica's little boy!

14
00:01:33,090 --> 00:01:36,856
-Look, he's got Ross' haircut.
-Let me see.

15
00:01:37,261 --> 00:01:40,321
Oh, God!
Is he just the sweetest thing?

16
00:01:40,597 --> 00:01:43,828
You must just wanna kiss him all over.

17
00:01:47,504 --> 00:01:49,870
That would be nice.

18
00:01:52,976 --> 00:01:54,068
-Pardon?
-Nothing.

19
00:01:54,278 --> 00:01:56,906
Just a little extra air in my mouth.

20
00:02:01,885 --> 00:02:05,377
Chan, can you help me out?
I'll pay you back.

21
00:02:05,589 --> 00:02:10,049
Right. Including the waffles
last week, you now owe me...

22
00:02:10,461 --> 00:02:12,691
...17 jillion dollars.

23
00:02:13,363 --> 00:02:17,925
-Really, I'll pay you back this time.
-Where's this money coming from?

24
00:02:18,135 --> 00:02:21,593
I'm helping out at the NYU
Med School with research.

25
00:02:21,805 --> 00:02:23,432
What kind of research?

26
00:02:25,409 --> 00:02:27,468
Just, you know, science.

27
00:02:28,178 --> 00:02:29,805
Science.

28
00:02:31,715 --> 00:02:34,240
Yeah, I think I've heard of that.

29
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:39,018
It's a fertility study.

30
00:02:39,456 --> 00:02:44,553
Joey, please tell me you're only
donating your time.

31
00:02:45,796 --> 00:02:48,924
Actually, a little more than that.

32
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:54,429
Thank you, God.
This will bring us so much joy.

33
00:02:54,872 --> 00:02:57,534
Come on, it's not that big a deal.

34
00:02:57,741 --> 00:03:00,301
I just go down there
every other day...

35
00:03:00,511 --> 00:03:03,605
...and make my contribution
to the project.

36
00:03:03,814 --> 00:03:06,578
But at the end of two weeks,
I get $700!

37
00:03:07,751 --> 00:03:11,016
You're gonna be making money
hand over fist.

38
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:15,115
That's funny. Very funny.

39
00:03:15,659 --> 00:03:21,097
This is great. I actually know
somebody who loves what they do.

40
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:27,363
But what do you do to unwind
after a tough day at work?

41
00:03:30,140 --> 00:03:32,631
Okay, we got the coleslaw and buns.

42
00:03:32,843 --> 00:03:37,246
The ground-up flesh
of formerly cute cows and turkeys.

43
00:03:38,482 --> 00:03:41,451
I just love barbecuing with you.

44
00:03:42,219 --> 00:03:44,210
Men are here!

45
00:03:49,393 --> 00:03:50,883
We make fire.

46
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,520
Cook meat.

47
00:03:54,731 --> 00:03:57,723
Put out fire by peeing,
no get invited back.

48
00:03:57,935 --> 00:03:59,300
Cute.

49
00:03:59,503 --> 00:04:02,404
-Melanie called. She'll be late.
-Okay.

50
00:04:02,606 --> 00:04:07,703
How are things going? Is she
becoming your "special someone"?

51
00:04:09,112 --> 00:04:12,013
I don't know. She's pretty great.

52
00:04:12,216 --> 00:04:15,982
What does she think of
your little science project?

53
00:04:16,787 --> 00:04:21,087
You think I'd tell a girl I like
that I'm also seeing a cup?

54
00:04:24,194 --> 00:04:25,684
Man's got a point.

55
00:04:25,963 --> 00:04:29,592
The tough thing is,
she really wants to have sex.

56
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,700
Crazy bitch.

57
00:04:36,873 --> 00:04:40,400
I got a week left to go.
According to the rules...

58
00:04:40,644 --> 00:04:46,173
...I can't conduct personal
experiments, if you know what I mean.

59
00:04:46,383 --> 00:04:50,046
Joey, we always know what you mean.

60
00:04:57,361 --> 00:05:00,853
How long did you think
this barbecue would last?

61
00:05:01,064 --> 00:05:05,592
-I'm going to China.
-Jeez, you say one thing, and...

62
00:05:06,303 --> 00:05:10,330
-China?
-For the museum. Someone found a bone.

63
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:12,735
They don't want us to have it.

64
00:05:12,943 --> 00:05:18,381
I'm going to try to persuade them.
It's a whole big bone thing.

65
00:05:18,582 --> 00:05:20,982
Anyway, I'll be gone for a week.

66
00:05:21,184 --> 00:05:26,486
If you want to reach me, you can't.
So here's my itinerary.

67
00:05:27,557 --> 00:05:30,390
-Here's a picture of me.
-Oh, let me see.

68
00:05:30,894 --> 00:05:35,957
Could you show it to Ben every now
and then so he doesn't forget me?

69
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:39,563
"Hi, Ben. I'm your father."

70
00:05:41,872 --> 00:05:44,033
"I am The Head!"

71
00:05:49,446 --> 00:05:52,415
This barbecue's gonna be very fun.

72
00:05:52,616 --> 00:05:56,313
I wanted to wish Rachel
a happy birthday before I left.

73
00:05:56,520 --> 00:06:01,355
-She's out having drinks with Carl.
-Hey, who's Carl?

74
00:06:04,061 --> 00:06:06,529
That guy she met at the coffeehouse.

75
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:11,292
-There's this guy she met at...
-The coffeehouse? Right.

76
00:06:11,501 --> 00:06:13,560
So you do know who he is.

77
00:06:17,407 --> 00:06:19,841
I'll go say goodbye to the guys.

78
00:06:20,043 --> 00:06:23,410
Hey, you know what?
Tell them that bone story.

79
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:33,753
-I have to go to China.
-The country?

80
00:06:34,825 --> 00:06:39,262
No, this big pile of dishes
in my mom's breakfront.

81
00:06:40,097 --> 00:06:41,792
Do you know who Carl is?

82
00:06:41,998 --> 00:06:46,458
Let's see. Alvin, Simon, Theodore...
No.

83
00:06:47,838 --> 00:06:50,534
Rachel's having
drinks with him tonight.

84
00:06:50,741 --> 00:06:54,370
How can she, when she's never
shown interest in you?

85
00:06:55,078 --> 00:06:57,706
-Forget about her.
-He's right.

86
00:06:57,914 --> 00:07:00,883
Please move on. Go to China.
Eat Chinese food.

87
00:07:01,385 --> 00:07:04,445
Of course, there
they just call it "food."

88
00:07:04,654 --> 00:07:08,283
Yeah, I guess. I don't know.

89
00:07:08,558 --> 00:07:12,119
All right, just give her this
for me, okay?

90
00:07:12,329 --> 00:07:15,924
We're looking out for you.
We want you to be happy.

91
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:20,627
I may only have a couple beers
in me, but I love you.

92
00:07:22,472 --> 00:07:24,406
I'm still on my first.

93
00:07:27,344 --> 00:07:29,642
I just think you're nice.

94
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:40,153
That's when we started
this fruit basket business.

95
00:07:40,357 --> 00:07:44,953
We call ourselves
"The Three Basketeers."

96
00:07:45,195 --> 00:07:48,596
Like "The Three Musketeers,"
only with fruit.

97
00:07:54,938 --> 00:07:57,873
-How do you want your burgers?
-Presents first!

98
00:07:58,074 --> 00:08:00,872
We're doing presents first.

99
00:08:02,446 --> 00:08:06,542
Hey, hold on there, tiger.
How are you holding up?

100
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:10,618
Well, not so good.
She thinks tonight we're gonna...

101
00:08:10,821 --> 00:08:15,121
...complete the transaction,
if you know what... And you do.

102
00:08:15,325 --> 00:08:18,886
Have you ever thought about
being there for her?

103
00:08:19,362 --> 00:08:21,227
What do you mean?

104
00:08:24,734 --> 00:08:28,465
You know, just be there for her.

105
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,304
Not following you.

106
00:08:35,445 --> 00:08:37,470
Think about it.

107
00:08:41,718 --> 00:08:47,520
Okay. I'm guessing this is from...

108
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:53,621
-Thank you, Melanie.
-This one right here is from me.

109
00:08:53,830 --> 00:08:58,733
Okay. It's light. It rattles.

110
00:08:58,969 --> 00:08:59,958
It's...

111
00:09:01,638 --> 00:09:03,936
...Travel Scrabble!

112
00:09:07,143 --> 00:09:08,906
Thank you.

113
00:09:12,415 --> 00:09:14,042
This one's from Joey.

114
00:09:14,251 --> 00:09:19,052
It feels like a book, I think it's
a book. And it's a book!

115
00:09:19,256 --> 00:09:21,156
It's Dr. Seuss!

116
00:09:22,292 --> 00:09:25,853
That book got me through
some tough times.

117
00:09:26,429 --> 00:09:29,057
There's a little child
inside this man.

118
00:09:29,266 --> 00:09:32,963
The doctors say if they remove it,
he'll die.

119
00:09:35,138 --> 00:09:37,231
-Who's this from?
-From Ross.

120
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:47,544
Oh, my God! He remembered!

121
00:09:47,984 --> 00:09:50,680
-Remembered what?
-It was months ago.

122
00:09:50,954 --> 00:09:54,390
We walked by this antique store.
I saw this pin.

123
00:09:54,658 --> 00:09:59,322
I told him it was like one
my grandma had when I was little.

124
00:09:59,563 --> 00:10:02,031
I can't believe he remembered!

125
00:10:02,232 --> 00:10:05,827
Well, sure, but can you
play it on a plane?

126
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:14,708
It's so pretty!
This must've cost him a fortune.

127
00:10:14,911 --> 00:10:16,071
I can't believe it.

128
00:10:16,279 --> 00:10:19,271
Remember when he
fell in love with Carol...

129
00:10:19,482 --> 00:10:22,940
...and bought her that
expensive crystal duck?

130
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:25,684
What did you just say?

131
00:10:37,233 --> 00:10:39,167
Crystal duck.

132
00:10:42,906 --> 00:10:48,538
No, no, no. The "love" part?

133
00:10:54,818 --> 00:11:00,723
-Oh, my God!
-Oh, no, no, no.

134
00:11:01,558 --> 00:11:06,621
That's good. Just keep rubbing
your head. That'll turn back time.

135
00:11:12,902 --> 00:11:16,338
This is unbelievable.
I mean, this is unbelievable!

136
00:11:16,539 --> 00:11:19,167
I know.
This is really, really huge.

137
00:11:19,376 --> 00:11:23,836
No, it's not. It's small.
It's tiny. It's petite. It's wee.

138
00:11:24,047 --> 00:11:29,041
I don't think any of our lives
will ever be the same ever again.

139
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:33,016
Is there a mute button on this woman?

140
00:11:33,223 --> 00:11:36,852
I think this is so great.
I mean, you and Ross!

141
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:40,029
-Did you have any idea?
-No, none!

142
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:44,098
My first night in the city,
he mentioned asking me out...

143
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:46,291
...but nothing ever happened.

144
00:11:46,503 --> 00:11:49,666
What else did he say?
Does he wanna go out?

145
00:11:49,873 --> 00:11:52,307
Given that he's in love with you...

146
00:11:52,509 --> 00:11:55,910
...he wouldn't mind getting
a cup of coffee.

147
00:11:56,279 --> 00:12:01,239
Ross? All this time?
I've gotta talk to him.

148
00:12:01,451 --> 00:12:04,420
-He's in China!
-The country.

149
00:12:07,691 --> 00:12:09,124
Is his flight gone?

150
00:12:09,325 --> 00:12:12,385
Yes! He's watching a woman do this:

151
00:12:12,595 --> 00:12:13,584
He's gone!

152
00:12:13,797 --> 00:12:16,493
His flight doesn't leave
for 45 minutes.

153
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:20,602
-What about time difference?
-From here to the airport?

154
00:12:21,805 --> 00:12:24,365
-You'll never make it!
-I've gotta try.

155
00:12:24,574 --> 00:12:26,565
What'll you say to him?

156
00:12:26,776 --> 00:12:29,438
-I don't know.
-Then you shouldn't go.

157
00:12:29,646 --> 00:12:33,309
Right. If you're gonna
break his heart, that can wait.

158
00:12:33,616 --> 00:12:35,607
But if it's good, tell him now.

159
00:12:35,819 --> 00:12:40,654
-Maybe I'll know when I see him.
-All right, does this help?

160
00:12:46,629 --> 00:12:51,965
No. Look, all I know is, I cannot
wait a week. This is just too big.

161
00:12:52,168 --> 00:12:56,264
I've just gotta talk to him.
Okay, I'll see you later.

162
00:12:56,473 --> 00:13:00,136
Rachel, I love you!
Deal with me first!

163
00:13:12,622 --> 00:13:13,611
All right.

164
00:13:18,928 --> 00:13:22,625
-Ross! Excuse me, pardon me.
-Your boarding pass?

165
00:13:22,832 --> 00:13:24,766
I need to talk to my friend.

166
00:13:24,968 --> 00:13:28,904
Sorry, you're not allowed here
without a pass.

167
00:13:29,105 --> 00:13:32,336
He's right there,
in the blue jacket! Can I?

168
00:13:32,542 --> 00:13:34,510
I'm sorry. Federal regulations!

169
00:13:34,711 --> 00:13:38,670
Then could you please
just give him a message for me?

170
00:13:38,982 --> 00:13:42,941
-This is very important.
-All right. What's the message?

171
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:45,749
I don't know.

172
00:13:47,690 --> 00:13:52,457
Excuse me, sir! Excuse me, sir?
I have a message for you.

173
00:13:52,695 --> 00:13:56,995
Rachel loved the present.
She'll see you when you get back.

174
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,827
What?

175
00:13:59,803 --> 00:14:02,863
Toby, I don't know
what she's talking about.

176
00:14:03,173 --> 00:14:07,507
There's no Rachel.
Don't give me that deep freeze.

177
00:14:16,352 --> 00:14:20,812
Oh, Joey, Joey, Joey!

178
00:14:21,024 --> 00:14:24,619
I think I blacked out there
for a minute.

179
00:14:25,662 --> 00:14:27,687
It was nothing.

180
00:14:27,897 --> 00:14:31,890
Well, now we gotta
find something fun for you.

181
00:14:35,371 --> 00:14:36,838
You know what?

182
00:14:38,741 --> 00:14:42,404
Forget about me.
Let's give you another turn.

183
00:14:44,981 --> 00:14:48,815
-Me, again?
-Sure. Why not?

184
00:14:51,421 --> 00:14:57,417
Boy, somebody's gonna get
a big fruit basket tomorrow!

185
00:15:01,264 --> 00:15:06,395
I gotta tell you, you are nothing like
I thought you'd be.

186
00:15:06,603 --> 00:15:07,968
How do you mean?

187
00:15:08,171 --> 00:15:12,608
I had you pegged as a guy
who's always, "Me, me, me!"

188
00:15:12,876 --> 00:15:16,073
But you, you're a giver.

189
00:15:17,513 --> 00:15:20,311
You're the most generous man
I ever met.

190
00:15:20,516 --> 00:15:23,542
I mean, you're practically a woman.

191
00:15:31,494 --> 00:15:34,725
-You're just saying that.
-No.

192
00:15:36,366 --> 00:15:38,061
<i>A woman!</i>

193
00:15:48,912 --> 00:15:51,278
-So?
-I missed him.

194
00:15:51,481 --> 00:15:53,915
-I'm so sorry.
-That's too bad.

195
00:15:54,117 --> 00:15:55,778
Yeah, right.

196
00:15:56,452 --> 00:15:58,545
No, I feel bad for her. I do.

197
00:15:58,755 --> 00:16:02,191
I can think of somebody
other than myself.

198
00:16:02,392 --> 00:16:04,451
All right, I'm going to bed.

199
00:16:06,062 --> 00:16:09,463
-Happy birthday. Hang in there.
-Thanks.

200
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:11,422
Yes!

201
00:16:13,836 --> 00:16:15,167
Pizza coupons.

202
00:16:20,143 --> 00:16:24,102
Okay. You guys want help
cleaning up this mess?

203
00:16:24,314 --> 00:16:25,872
That'd be great.

204
00:16:29,185 --> 00:16:32,416
So, Rach, you wanna save
this wrapping paper?

205
00:16:32,622 --> 00:16:37,423
Are you gonna go for it with Ross
or should I throw it out?

206
00:16:40,296 --> 00:16:44,255
I don't know. I don't know.

207
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:46,958
Thought about it
all the way there...

208
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:52,073
...and I thought about it all the way
back. You know, it's Ross!

209
00:16:52,275 --> 00:16:54,675
You know what I mean? It's Ross.

210
00:16:54,877 --> 00:16:56,606
-Sure!
-Sure.

211
00:16:56,813 --> 00:17:02,012
I don't know. This is just
my initial gut feeling...

212
00:17:02,552 --> 00:17:06,579
...but I'm thinking
it'd be really great.

213
00:17:06,789 --> 00:17:10,384
Oh, my God, me too!
We'd be like friends-in-law!

214
00:17:11,661 --> 00:17:14,824
The best part is you already
know all about him.

215
00:17:15,031 --> 00:17:17,158
You start on the 15th date.

216
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:20,768
But it would be like
starting on the 15th date.

217
00:17:21,671 --> 00:17:23,571
Another good point.

218
00:17:23,773 --> 00:17:28,005
I mean, on the 15th date,
you're already in a very...

219
00:17:28,211 --> 00:17:31,442
..."relationship-y" place.
You're committed.

220
00:17:34,951 --> 00:17:37,351
What happens if it doesn't work out?

221
00:17:37,553 --> 00:17:40,522
-Why isn't it working out?
-Sometimes it doesn't.

222
00:17:40,757 --> 00:17:44,488
Is he not cute enough?
Does he not make enough money?

223
00:17:44,694 --> 00:17:47,663
-No, I'm just...
-Maybe there's someone else.

224
00:17:47,864 --> 00:17:52,528
-Is there someone else?
-No, there is no one else.

225
00:17:52,735 --> 00:17:55,363
Then why are you dumping my brother?

226
00:18:06,015 --> 00:18:08,711
Hey, big... Spender!

227
00:18:11,654 --> 00:18:13,212
She's still asleep.

228
00:18:13,523 --> 00:18:18,153
-So how'd it go?
-You know how you think you're great?

229
00:18:18,361 --> 00:18:22,388
The fact you'd even ask
shows how little you know me.

230
00:18:22,598 --> 00:18:27,433
Last night I couldn't do the thing
that usually makes me great.

231
00:18:27,637 --> 00:18:30,071
So I had to do all this other stuff.

232
00:18:30,273 --> 00:18:33,071
And the response I got! Man, oh, man!

233
00:18:33,309 --> 00:18:36,335
It was like a ticker-tape parade!

234
00:18:37,413 --> 00:18:42,316
I know. My room's very, very close
to the parade route.

235
00:18:46,823 --> 00:18:50,418
It was amazing, and not just for her.
For me too!

236
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:53,857
It's like, all of a sudden
I'm blind...

237
00:18:54,063 --> 00:18:56,861
...but all my other senses
are heightened.

238
00:18:57,066 --> 00:18:59,967
It's like I was able
to appreciate it...

239
00:19:00,269 --> 00:19:02,203
...on another level.

240
00:19:04,774 --> 00:19:09,711
-I didn't know you had another level.
-I know. Neither did I!

241
00:19:11,714 --> 00:19:14,649
Is something going on with O.J.?

242
00:19:25,061 --> 00:19:27,586
Hey, great skirt. Birthday present?

243
00:19:27,797 --> 00:19:28,957
-From who?
-You.

244
00:19:29,165 --> 00:19:31,861
I exchanged the blouse you got me.

245
00:19:33,102 --> 00:19:34,694
Well, it's the thought.

246
00:19:35,538 --> 00:19:39,907
Doesn't Ross' flight get in
in a couple hours? At gate 27B?

247
00:19:41,444 --> 00:19:45,813
Yeah. Monica, you know, I've been
thinking about it.

248
00:19:46,048 --> 00:19:49,313
I've decided this Ross thing
is not a good idea.

249
00:19:49,519 --> 00:19:50,508
Why?

250
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:54,315
I feel like I wouldn't
just be going out with him.

251
00:19:54,524 --> 00:19:58,324
I'd be going out with all of you.
There'd be pressure...

252
00:19:58,561 --> 00:20:00,358
No pressure, no pressure!

253
00:20:02,064 --> 00:20:04,897
Nothing has happened,
and you're already so...

254
00:20:05,101 --> 00:20:09,060
I'm not "so." Okay, I was a teensy
bit weird at first...

255
00:20:09,272 --> 00:20:12,400
...but I'll be good. I promise.

256
00:20:17,413 --> 00:20:19,938
-Who is it?
-It's me, Carl.

257
00:20:20,249 --> 00:20:23,047
-Come on up.
-Behind my brother's back?

258
00:20:24,921 --> 00:20:29,984
Is the kind of crazy thing
you won't be hearing from me.

259
00:20:42,038 --> 00:20:45,269
-Seven hundred bucks!
-All right, you did it!

260
00:20:45,474 --> 00:20:47,772
Do we have any fruit?

261
00:20:50,046 --> 00:20:51,946
Man, hell of a two weeks.

262
00:20:52,215 --> 00:20:55,150
You know what?
I feel I learned something.

263
00:20:55,351 --> 00:20:57,945
You'll stick with this
"all for her" thing?

264
00:20:58,187 --> 00:20:59,779
What are you, crazy?

265
00:21:00,289 --> 00:21:05,317
When a blind man gets his sight back,
does he walk around like this?

266
00:21:10,032 --> 00:21:13,729
If I see one more picture
of Ed Begley Jr...

267
00:21:13,970 --> 00:21:18,464
...in that stupid electric car,
I'm gonna shoot myself!

268
00:21:19,575 --> 00:21:23,443
I'm not against
environmental issues, per se...

269
00:21:23,646 --> 00:21:25,307
...it's just that guy!

270
00:21:25,748 --> 00:21:29,741
I can't believe you'd rather
go out with him than me.

271
00:21:30,186 --> 00:21:33,178
Excuse me, I'm trying
to have a date here.

272
00:21:33,656 --> 00:21:36,750
Fine. Just stop thinking about me.

273
00:21:39,328 --> 00:21:41,489
Can't do it, can you?

274
00:21:42,265 --> 00:21:44,597
I'm thinking about you. So what?

275
00:21:44,834 --> 00:21:47,997
I don't get it.
What do you see in this guy?

276
00:21:49,171 --> 00:21:51,662
Happens to be a very nice guy.

277
00:21:51,874 --> 00:21:55,002
I mean, come on, buddy!
Get a real car!

278
00:21:57,947 --> 00:22:01,644
Rachel, come on. Give us a chance.

279
00:22:02,351 --> 00:22:03,943
Ross, it's too hard.

280
00:22:04,153 --> 00:22:08,852
Why, because it'll get weird
for everyone else? This is about us.

281
00:22:09,058 --> 00:22:12,494
I've been in love with you
since the ninth grade.

282
00:22:12,795 --> 00:22:17,494
You're like my best friend.
If we broke up, and I lost you...

283
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:19,497
What makes you think that?

284
00:22:19,735 --> 00:22:24,035
Have you been involved
where you haven't broken up?

285
00:22:26,108 --> 00:22:27,097
No.

286
00:22:27,943 --> 00:22:31,743
But it only has to happen once.

287
00:22:32,014 --> 00:22:36,747
You and I both know we are perfect
for each other. Right?

288
00:22:36,952 --> 00:22:41,321
So the only question is:
Are you attracted to me?

289
00:22:42,425 --> 00:22:44,393
I don't know.

290
00:22:45,895 --> 00:22:48,864
I mean, I've never looked at you
that way before.

291
00:22:49,632 --> 00:22:51,259
Well, start looking.

292
00:23:02,111 --> 00:23:04,136
-Wow.
-Exactly!

293
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:06,314
And I'm gonna be the guy...

294
00:23:06,582 --> 00:23:09,813
...caught behind this hammerhead
in traffic!

295
00:23:12,054 --> 00:23:14,716
Right! You're right.

296
00:23:15,558 --> 00:23:16,616
You know what?

297
00:23:16,826 --> 00:23:20,159
I'm supposed to pick up
a friend at the airport.

298
00:23:20,396 --> 00:23:22,421
I am so sorry!

299
00:23:22,665 --> 00:23:25,862
If you wanna finish your drinks,
please do.

300
00:23:26,068 --> 00:23:29,560
-I'm sorry, I gotta go. I'm sorry.
-But...

301
00:23:34,910 --> 00:23:37,811
-Where are you going?
-To get Ross.

302
00:23:38,013 --> 00:23:40,379
-My God, this is so exciting!
-I know.

303
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:44,917
If you want the rest of my date,
I'm not gonna finish it.

304
00:23:45,388 --> 00:23:50,917
-Rachel, he's not a sandwich.
-No, he's a banker with opera tickets.

305
00:23:52,228 --> 00:23:54,059
Hello!

306
00:23:57,566 --> 00:23:59,431
-Where you going?
-Airport.

307
00:23:59,668 --> 00:24:02,933
You can't tell him.
There's so much I haven't done.

308
00:24:03,139 --> 00:24:06,108
I haven't watched <i>Baywatch</i>
with Yasmine Bleeth!

309
00:24:07,743 --> 00:24:11,679
Chandler, relax. This is a good
going to the airport.

310
00:24:12,214 --> 00:24:15,911
Oh, well then fly, good woman,
fly like the wind.

311
00:24:16,118 --> 00:24:19,087
-I'm flying!
-Tell him I'm the one who blew it!

312
00:24:20,556 --> 00:24:25,323
Yes, another successful case
for the love doctor.

313
00:24:33,636 --> 00:24:36,969
Excuse me! Pardon me.
Excuse me. Sorry.

314
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:40,868
Toby, for God's sake,
will you let it go?

315
00:24:41,143 --> 00:24:42,610
There's no Rachel!

316
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:50,485
Hey! I got that.

317
00:24:51,020 --> 00:24:53,181
-Thanks, sweetie.
-No problem.

318
00:24:59,128 --> 00:25:01,790
I can't wait for you
to meet my friends.

319
00:25:01,997 --> 00:25:04,693
You don't think they'll judge me?

320
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:07,664
-No, they will. I just...
-Can't wait!

321
00:25:07,870 --> 00:25:10,361
Come on, they're gonna love you.
